### 1.6 What is TCP/IP?

**30-second interview answer:**
> "TCP/IP is the foundational communication protocol of the internet and most networks. TCP handles reliable, ordered delivery — it does a three-way handshake before sending data. IP handles the addressing and routing of packets. Together they ensure data gets from A to B correctly."

**TCP vs UDP:**

| | TCP | UDP |
|--|-----|-----|
| **Type** | Connection-oriented | Connectionless |
| **Reliability** | Guaranteed delivery | Best-effort |
| **Speed** | Slower (handshake) | Faster (no handshake) |
| **Use cases** | Email, web, file transfer | VoIP, video streaming, DNS |

**Three-way handshake:** SYN → SYN-ACK → ACK

