> "We had a situation where the company website went down during a critical business period. I immediately acknowledged the issue to the stakeholders so they knew it was being worked on. I checked the server status, reviewed the logs, and identified it was a web server configuration issue after a recent update. I coordinated with the Web Dev team, provided regular 30-minute updates to management, and the site was restored within the SLA window. The key was communication — keeping everyone informed while the technical work happened."

