### 7.2 Command Line Cheat Sheet

| Command | Why you use it |
|---------|---------------|
| `ipconfig /all` | Full network info including MAC, DHCP server |
| `ipconfig /release` | Drop current IP lease |
| `ipconfig /renew` | Request new IP from DHCP |
| `ipconfig /flushdns` | Clear DNS cache |
| `ping 8.8.8.8 -t` | Continuous ping to check stability |
| `ping google.com` | Test DNS resolution + internet |
| `tracert google.com` | Find which hop (router) is failing |
| `nslookup google.com` | Check what IP DNS returns for a name |
| `whoami` | Check if local, domain, or Azure account |
| `whoami /groups` | See all security groups the user is in |
| `gpupdate /force` | Apply Group Policy immediately |
| `net user [username] /domain` | Check account status, last password change |
| `sfc /scannow` | Repair corrupted Windows system files |
| `chkdsk /f` | Fix hard drive errors |
| `netstat -an` | See all active network connections/ports |
| `arp -a` | Show ARP table (IP to MAC mappings) |
| `hostname` | Show the computer's name |

